text: I see difference between Docker image created by “make docker” , and the sample provided by “fabric-cop/docker/fabric-cop”.  Image created by “make docker” seems to assume COP_HOME is “/etc/hyperledger/cop” while the sample assumes to have “~/.cop” for certificate and keys, and “/config” for cop.json configuration file.  I think we should use “make docker” one, because it seems light weight (only consumes 50MB, and comes with busybox only, i.e. more secure).
